Note:
Runa Standard Library: Location Services

Production-grade location services providing comprehensive GPS,
mapping, and geospatial capabilities across mobile platforms.

Features:
- High-accuracy GPS positioning with multiple providers
- Cross-platform geolocation (Android LocationManager, iOS Core Location)
- Geofencing with entry/exit notifications
- Route planning and navigation assistance
- Geocoding (address to coordinates) and reverse geocoding
- Distance calculations and bearing computations
- Location history tracking and analytics
- Battery-optimized location strategies
- Indoor positioning and beacon integration
- Offline map support and tile caching
- Real-time location sharing
- Location-based contextual services
- Privacy-compliant location handling
- Background location updates with power management
- Integration with mapping services (Google Maps, Apple Maps, OpenStreetMap)
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "../../datetime" as DateTime
Import "../../string" as String
Import "math/core" as Math

Note: Core location types
Type called "LocationProvider":
    provider_name as String
    provider_type as String
    accuracy as String
    power_consumption as String
    supports_altitude as Boolean
    supports_bearing as Boolean
    supports_speed as Boolean
    is_enabled as Boolean
    last_known_location as Location

Type called "Location":
    latitude as Float
    longitude as Float
    altitude as Float
    accuracy as Float
    vertical_accuracy as Float
    bearing as Float
    speed as Float
    timestamp as DateTime.DateTime
    provider as String
    extras as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "LocationRequest":
    priority as String
    interval as Integer
    fastest_interval as Integer
    max_wait_time as Integer
    num_updates as Integer
    expiration_duration as Integer
    smallest_displacement as Float

Type called "LocationResult":
